- Create ./app/.env file
- Register for cloudinary
- Put environment variables for cloudinary in ./app/.env
e.g
** .env file **
CLOUD_NAME=<cloudinary cloud_name>
API_KEY=<cloudinary api_key>
API_SECRET=<cloudinary api_secret>
** .env file end **

Start containers
$ docker-compose up --build -d 
Attach to nodeservers stdin
$ docker attach <nodeserver container name>
Access nodeserver, install modules, etc
$ docker exec -it <nodeserver container name> bash
Access database
$ docker exec -it <databaserver container name> bash